textBeforeTable: » « Tuesday, October 1 PREVIOUS EVENTS FREE DOCENT TOURS CALENDAR Monday, November 4, 2013 - 10:00am Event-Date:  Dr. Petti teaches anatomy and physiology, and human dissection at San Diego Miramar College. He has contributed to numerous college anatomy textbooks, and is a frequent guest lecturer at national conferences and universities. Free admission. Italy's medieval universities established the study of human anatomy for medical professionals. To heighten their art, Renaissance masters clandestinely studied anatomy through human dissection. This talk will examine the profound nexus between art and science, and the history of anatomy education in the university. Speaker: Kevin Petti, Professor, Departments
